Calculating diffuse and specular intensities using vector dot products in HLSL:

```hlsl
// HLSL Lighting calculations
float3 CalculatePhong(float3 Normal, float3 LightDir, float3 ViewDir) {
    // Diffuse component (Lambertian)
    float DiffuseIntensity = max(dot(Normal, LightDir), 0.0f);

    // Specular component
    float3 ReflectionVector = reflect(-LightDir, Normal);
    float SpecularIntensity = pow(max(dot(ReflectionVector, ViewDir), 0.0f), 32); // 32 is shininess

    return (DiffuseIntensity * float3(0.8f, 0.8f, 0.8f)) + (SpecularIntensity * float3(1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f));
}
```
